customLinks.clientQuery:
let Subscriptions = Regex.Match(properties, "Subscriptions=\[(.*)\]").Groups[1].Value
let TenantId = Regex.Match(properties, "Tenant=\[(.*)\]").Groups[1].Value
let RequestUrl = Regex.Match(properties, "RequestAddressUrl=\[(.*)\]").Groups[1].Value
let DataType = Regex.Match(properties, "DataType=\[(.*)\]").Groups[1].Value
select PreciseTimeStamp, durationMilliseconds, Tenant, context, exception, Subscriptions, TenantId, RequestUrl, DataType
customLinks.title: Failed PAS Calls

value:
groupby PreciseTimeStamp.roundDown("PT5M") as X
let Count = Count()

monitors.customMessage: This incident indicates that a particular type of PAS call (RoleAssignments, ClassicAdministrator, CustomRoleDefinition) has a high failure rate. If Classic Administrator calls are constantly failing, it can be disabled through hot config RBAC/IgnoreClassicAdministratorCalls
monitors.description:

monitors.description:
Use TSG PAS call failures [PasCallDurationMs] in OneNote. Please note built-in role definitions do not have a subscription/tenant as they're constant for the whole Azure.

Built-in role definitions are synced every 24h on each query node. If some node fails to sync them 2 days in a row, we may have deployed wrong bits or use a bad cert to communicate with PAS endpoint. It also can be that PAS regions are having some issues, you can blacklist a particular region through a hotconfig.
